docs.lead_paragraph: There are wine bars and a cycling studio along the riverfront in Long Island City, among gleaming high-rise apartment buildings with views of Midtown Manhattan. docs.abstract: Crystal City, a declining neighborhood in Arlington, Va., cheered Amazon’s arrival on Tuesday. It’s getting a new name — National Landing — to go along with its victory.
docs.snippet: Crystal City, a declining neighborhood in Arlington, Va., cheered Amazon’s arrival on Tuesday. It’s getting a new name — National Landing — to go along with its victory.
docs.lead_paragraph: ARLINGTON, Va. — Over the past few months, murals had started appearing on a fence surrounding an empty brick warehouse in the Crystal City neighborhood of Arlington. Sporting geometric shapes and adorned with hanging bicycles, the murals also displayed aspirational slogans in big black letters like “What If?” and “Why Not?”

docs.abstract: Wall Street has dominated New York’s economy for too long. Amazon’s HQ2 is a huge opportunity to diversify.
docs.snippet: Wall Street has dominated New York’s economy for too long. Amazon’s HQ2 is a huge opportunity to diversify.
docs.lead_paragraph: For decades, experts have called for the diversification of the New York City economy. In the wake of postwar deindustrialization, our reliance on Wall Street and the financial industry in general had by the 1990s left our city disproportionately vulnerable to swings in the financial markets. We have experienced significant downturns that today feel like distant memories but could certainly return. I know this from my own experience as director of planning for Manhattan after Sept. 11.

headline.main: New York City Needs Amazon as Much as Amazon Needs Us

docs.abstract: Amazon is not in the business of saving your hometown.
docs.snippet: Amazon is not in the business of saving your hometown.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon could have transformed a city. It could have created 50,000 high-paying jobs in a place with higher-than-average unemployment. It could have become the largest employer in a midsize city, or the central player in a new regional tech hub.

headline.main: Dominating Retail? Yes. Reviving a City? No Thanks.
